tant (it's a benzhydryl carbocation). The nucleophile (pyridinoxide) attacks this carbocation. This is essentially the second step of an SN1 mechanism - nucleophilic capture of a carbocation. But since the carbocation is given as a reactant, the mechanism is simply nucleophilic addition to a carbocation.\n\nThe reaction center: Formation of C(20)-O(10) bond, where C20 was a carbocation and O10 was an oxyanion.\n\nFor the mechanistic class label, I'll go with \"nucleophilic_addition\" as this best describes the local transformation."
